s expected to get a medal, finished fifth in 52.68 seconds, just ahead of Shiann Salmon who was sixth with 53.29 seconds.\", \"from\": 232, \"to\": 422, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 232, \"end\": 247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rushell_Clayton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rushell Clayton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rushell_Clayton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rushell_Clayton\"}, {\"begin\": 375, \"end\": 388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shiann_Salmon\", \"score\": 0.9999999936123913, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shiann Salmon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shiann_Salmon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shiann_Salmon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McLaughlin-Levrone, who is unbeaten since 2019 and who had set the previous world record 50.65 seconds in June at the USA Trials, destroyed a quality field with 50.37 seconds.\", \"from\": 424, \"to\": 599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 542, \"end\": 545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9907571368099826, \"rank\": 0.005308377240552663, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her teammate Anna Cockrell was second with a lifetime best 51.87 seconds and World and European champion Femke Bol was third in 52.15seconds.\", \"from\": 601, \"to\": 742, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 614, \"end\": 627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Cockrell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Cockrell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Cockrell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Cockrell\"}, {\"begin\": 688, \"end\": 705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eur